  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Liprotamase consists of 3 soluble, non-porcine digestive enzymes, lipase, protease, and
      amylase, combined in a fixed ratio. Liprotamase is stable in the stomach and can be
      formulated without enteric coating for administration either as a capsule or as a dosing
      solution dissolved in water or juice. The purpose of the present study is to provide
      efficacy and safety data for a new, soluble formulation of liprotamase, Liprotamase Powder
      for Oral Solution, in Cystic Fibrosis patients with exocrine pancreatic insufficiency (EPI).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
